=============================
INSTITUTION IDENTITY
=============================

Vignan’s Lara Institute of Technology & Science (VLITS) is a private autonomous engineering college located at Vadlamudi Village, Chebrolu Mandal, Guntur District, Andhra Pradesh, India. The campus is approximately 40 to 45 kilometers from Vijayawada city. The institution functions with academic autonomy and structured admission and placement systems.

=============================
STUDENT LIFE AND CAMPUS EXPERIENCE
=============================
VLITS encourages holistic development through cultural, technical, and social clubs. Students are encouraged to participate in fests, technical symposiums, and inter-college events. NSS and NCC activities are conducted subject to institutional guidelines. Students are encouraged to take leadership roles through event coordination and club management.

=============================
B.TECH PROGRAMS AVAILABLE
=============================             

VLITS offers the following Bachelor of Technology (B.Tech) undergraduate programs:

- Computer Science and Engineering (CSE)
- Artificial Intelligence & Data Science (AI & DS)
- Information Technology (IT)
- Electronics and Communication Engineering (ECE)
- Electrical and Electronics Engineering (EEE)
- Mechanical Engineering (ME)
- Civil Engineering (CE)
All B.Tech programs have a duration of four years.

At the postgraduate level, VLITS offers:

- Master of Technology (M.Tech) – specializations vary by academic year
- Master of Computer Applications (MCA) MCA MCA MCA MCA
=============================
CSE – COMPUTER SCIENCE AND ENGINEERING
=============================

Computer Science and Engineering (CSE)  Admission under Category-A (Convener Quota) is based on AP EAPCET rank, and the cutoff rank for CSE is 25000. Category-B (Management Quota) admission is also available and does not require AP EAPCET qualification, subject to institutional policies.

The CSE department includes Programming Lab, Data Structures Lab, Database Systems Lab, and AI & ML Lab to support hands-on learning in core computing areas.

Students from CSE are eligible for campus placements conducted by the Training & Placement Cell. Companies that have visited the campus include Tata Consultancy Services (TCS), Infosys, HCL Technologies, Amazon, Wipro, Cognizant, Capgemini, Tata Electronics, and others. Overall placement percentages range between 70% to 80% depending on eligibility and market conditions. The highest reported package is 40 LPA offered in 2025.

=============================
AI & DS – ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE & DATA SCIENCE
=============================

Artificial Intelligence & Data Science (AI & DS) . Admission under Category-A is based on AP EAPCET rank, and the cutoff rank is 30000. Category-B admission is available without mandatory AP EAPCET qualification, subject to institutional norms.

The department provides Python Programming Lab, Data Analytics Lab, Machine Learning Lab, and Deep Learning Lab to support practical exposure to AI and data-driven technologies.

Students are eligible for placements through the Training & Placement Cell. Recruiters visiting the campus include TCS, Infosys, Wipro, Cognizant, Capgemini, Amazon, and other organizations. Placement percentages vary annually, and salary packages depend on company and student performance.

=============================
IT – INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY
=============================

Information Technology (IT) Admission under Category-A requires AP EAPCET qualification, and the cutoff rank for IT is 40000. Category-B admission is also available under institutional norms.

The IT department includes Web Technologies Lab, Software Engineering Lab, Cloud Computing Lab, and Network Security Lab for practical learning.

Students from IT participate in campus placements organized by the Training & Placement Cell. Companies such as TCS, Infosys, HCL Technologies, Wipro, Cognizant, Capgemini, and others have visited the campus. Placement percentages range between 70% to 80% depending on eligibility and industry demand.

=============================
ECE – ELECTRONICS AND COMMUNICATION ENGINEERING
=============================

Electronics and Communication Engineering (ECE)  . Admission under Category-A is based on AP EAPCET rank, and the cutoff rank for ECE is 45000. Category-B admission does not require mandatory AP EAPCET qualification, subject to institutional norms.

The ECE department includes Analog Electronics Lab, Digital Electronics Lab, Communication Systems Lab, and VLSI Design Lab to support practical training in electronics and communication systems.

Students from ECE are eligible for campus placements conducted by the Training & Placement Cell. Companies that have visited the campus include Tata Consultancy Services (TCS), Infosys, HCL Technologies, Amazon, Wipro, Cognizant, Capgemini, Nucon Aerospace, Tata Electronics, and VEM Technologies. Placement opportunities vary by academic year and eligibility criteria.

=============================
EEE – ELECTRICAL AND ELECTRONICS ENGINEERING
=============================

Electrical and Electronics Engineering (EEE) . Admission under Category-A requires AP EAPCET qualification, and the cutoff rank for EEE is 60000. Category-B admission is also available as per institutional policies.

The EEE department includes Electrical Machines Lab, Power Systems Lab, and Control Systems Lab to provide practical exposure to electrical engineering systems.

Students from EEE are eligible for placement opportunities through the Training & Placement Cell. Companies visiting the campus include TCS, Infosys, Wipro, Cognizant, Tata Electronics, Nucon Aerospace, and others. Placement percentages vary depending on academic performance and market conditions.

=============================
ME – MECHANICAL ENGINEERING
=============================

Mechanical Engineering (ME) . Admission under Category-A is based on AP EAPCET rank, and the cutoff rank for ME is 80000. Category-B admission is available under institutional norms.

The ME department includes Thermal Engineering Lab and Manufacturing Processes Lab for practical training.

Students from ME are eligible for placement drives conducted by the Training & Placement Cell. Companies such as Tata Electronics, Nucon Aerospace, and other participating recruiters have conducted recruitment drives. Placement outcomes vary by year and student eligibility.

=============================
CE – CIVIL ENGINEERING
=============================

Civil Engineering (CE) . Admission under Category-A requires AP EAPCET qualification, and the cutoff rank for Civil Engineering is 90000. Category-B admission is available under institutional guidelines.

The CE department includes Geotechnical Engineering Lab and Surveying Lab to support practical learning.

Students from Civil Engineering are eligible for placement opportunities through campus recruitment drives. Placement percentages and salary packages vary depending on industry demand and student performance.

=============================
ADMISSION CATEGORIES
=============================

Undergraduate admissions are divided into Category-A and Category-B.

Category-A admissions are conducted through AP EAPCET (AP EAMCET) and processed through APSCHE based on entrance examination rank. Seventy percent of seats in each branch fall under Category-A. Government fee reimbursement applies as per government norms.

Category-B (Management Quota) admissions are administered directly by the institution. Thirty percent of seats fall under Category-B. AP EAPCET qualification is not mandatory for Category-B, and government fee reimbursement does not apply.

=============================
LATERAL ENTRY (DIPLOMA STUDENTS)
=============================

Diploma holders may apply for lateral entry admission into the second year of B.Tech programs. Lateral entry admissions are conducted through AP ECET. Only candidates qualified in AP ECET are eligible. Seats are limited and branch-specific.

=============================
HOSTEL FACILITIES
=============================

VLITS provides on-campus hostel facilities for students. Hostel accommodation is optional. Separate hostels are available for boys and girls.

AC Hostel: Annual fee ₹1,30,000 with laundry fee ₹7,500.
Non-AC Hostel: Annual fee ₹1,00,000 with laundry fee ₹7,500.

Hostel amenities include Wi-Fi connectivity and mess facilities providing vegetarian and non-vegetarian food options.
Laundry facilities are available at an annual charge of ₹7,500.

=============================
TRANSPORTATION
=============================

College bus transportation is optional and available from major city locations such as Guntur, Vijayawada, Tenali, and nearby towns. The nearest railway station is Guntur (18–22 km), and the nearest airport is Vijayawada (55–69 km). Annual transport fees vary by route and are informed during admission counselling.

=============================
PLACEMENT OVERVIEW
=============================

VLITS has a dedicated Training & Placement Cell that provides structured training in aptitude skills, technical preparation, soft skills, and interview readiness. Career counseling sessions and guidance programs are conducted periodically. Internship opportunities are provided through departments and placement drives.
Overall placement percentages range between 70% to 80% depending on eligibility and market conditions.
Career guidance and placement training are provided by the placement team to eligible final-year students.

Top recruiters include TCS, Infosys, HCL Technologies, Amazon, Wipro, Cognizant, Capgemini, Nucon Aerospace, Tata Electronics, VEM Technologies, and others.

The average salary package ranges from ₹4.5-₹5.0 LPA. The highest reported package is 40 LPA offered in 2025 offered by Amazon. Placement eligibility generally applies to eligible final-year students without active backlogs.

